    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on)</p><p>Whilst the rice is cooking, cut your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>in half</p><p>Cut a piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) approx. the size of A3 paper, then lay the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>Tenderstem</strong> in the middle with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the Tenderstem to form a sealed parcel[s], then put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
