    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>coated chicken strips</strong> along with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>soy sauce</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side until golden and crispy and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy chicken</strong></p><p>Once crispy, transfer to a plate and set aside (save the pan!)</p>",
